<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1239,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
Total length 
<quantity box="[299,430,1239,1263]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.55" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="3.55" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.5">3.5–3.6mm</quantity>
. General color milky white with brown spots; eyes and ocelli light brown. Head with anterior margin produced and angled medially; pronotum approximately twice length of crown, margins of laterobasal angles exceeding width of head; scutellum with brown spot.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1239,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[324,399,1348,1372]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1873,1896]" captionTargetBox="[207,1362,1183,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1428,1169,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Balera fiuzai, sp. nov. 1 – 3: (1) habitus (dorsolateral view); (2) head and thorax (dorsal); (3) head (ventral). Habralebra gillettei Young 4 – 6: (4) habitus (dorsolateral view); (5) head and thorax (dorsal); (6) head (ventral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283590/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[414,443,1348,1372]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 37" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[267,1301,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1319,193,1411]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 37. Habralebra gillettei Young: (30) forewing; (31) hind wing; (32) pygofer (lateral); (33) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (34) style (ventral); (35) style (lateral); (36) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (37) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283593/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">30</figureCitation>
) milky white, basal margin of clavus with brown spot continuous with scutellar spot; small brown round spot near costal margin on basal third; brown spot on apex of cell cup, continuous with apical region of brachial cell, appendix and base of apical cells; transversal and MP 
<number box="[1081,1089,1435,1449]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
veins aligned; vein ScP+RA indistinct. 
<collectingCountry box="[273,329,1458,1482]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing (
<figureCitation box="[416,501,1458,1482]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 37" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[267,1301,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1319,193,1411]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 37. Habralebra gillettei Young: (30) forewing; (31) hind wing; (32) pygofer (lateral); (33) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (34) style (ventral); (35) style (lateral); (36) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (37) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283593/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[472,501,1458,1482]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
) with submarginal vein confluent with apical margin anteriorly to apex of vein MP 
<number box="[191,199,1510,1524]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
+CuA 
<number box="[268,276,1510,1524]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
; vein CuA 
<number box="[404,412,1510,1524]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
distinct from a point very close to vein MP 
<number box="[924,932,1510,1524]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
; vein CuP confluent with submarginal vein more basally than vein MP 
<number box="[452,460,1549,1563]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1239,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[395,475,1572,1596]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 37" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[267,1301,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1319,193,1411]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 37. Habralebra gillettei Young: (30) forewing; (31) hind wing; (32) pygofer (lateral); (33) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (34) style (ventral); (35) style (lateral); (36) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (37) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283593/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[446,475,1572,1596]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
) long, gradually tapering to apex; apex round; with internal folds from base to median third; apical third with external folds giving twisted aspect to apex; median third with five macrosetae distributed longitudinally, two basal most sided, each one, by small and stout seta; many long filiform setae following external margin from near basal margin to apex, where setae of various sizes can be found. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1311,1680,1704]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 37" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[267,1301,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1319,193,1411]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 37. Habralebra gillettei Young: (30) forewing; (31) hind wing; (32) pygofer (lateral); (33) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (34) style (ventral); (35) style (lateral); (36) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (37) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283593/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[1280,1311,1680,1704]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with internal and external folds, dorsal and ventral; internal process long with apex thin and twisted, extended ventrad; with five macrosetae, one near dorsal margin just basad of internal process and four on disc near midlength arranged transversally and, anteriorly to them, pair of filiform and short setae; group of filiform long setae on anteroventral region. Stylus (
<figureCitation box="[580,710,1824,1848]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 37" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[267,1301,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1319,193,1411]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 37. Habralebra gillettei Young: (30) forewing; (31) hind wing; (32) pygofer (lateral); (33) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (34) style (ventral); (35) style (lateral); (36) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (37) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283593/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Figs 34, 35</figureCitation>
) with distinct round preapical lobe, anterior branch curved with broad and trucate apex, with short spiniform projection. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[946,1029,1860,1884]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 37" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[267,1301,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1319,193,1411]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 37. Habralebra gillettei Young: (30) forewing; (31) hind wing; (32) pygofer (lateral); (33) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (34) style (ventral); (35) style (lateral); (36) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (37) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283593/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[1000,1029,1860,1884]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
) V-shaped. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1295,1427,1860,1884]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 37" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[267,1301,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1319,193,1411]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 37. Habralebra gillettei Young: (30) forewing; (31) hind wing; (32) pygofer (lateral); (33) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (34) style (ventral); (35) style (lateral); (36) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (37) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283593/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Figs 36, 37</figureCitation>
) compressed; preatrium narrow and long; dorsal apodeme short, similar in shape to robust “T”, in ventral view; stem long, sinuous, cylindrical with numerous small tubercles more concentrated on dorsobasal region, apex narrow and truncate; gonopore dorsoapical; base broad, bearing single ventral process, as long as stem, cylindrical and with sharp apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
