<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1537,1743]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1609,1634]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Comments.</emphasis>
The most evident differences in relation to previous descriptions of 
<taxonomicName box="[1118,1345,1610,1634]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Habralebra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gillettei">
<emphasis box="[1118,1345,1610,1634]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Habralebra gillettei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Young 
<number box="[151,209,1646,1670]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="1957.0">1957</number>
b, Dworakowska 
<number box="[403,460,1646,1670]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="1994.0">1994</number>
) are the number of macrosetae, the presence of filiform setae at the base of the pygofer and the thinner apex of the style. 
<taxonomicName box="[526,647,1682,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Habralebra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gillettei">
<emphasis box="[526,647,1682,1706]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">H. gillettei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, here recorded for the first time from Minas Gerais State, differs from the other species of the genus by having the apex of the style broadened and by the shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
